 Trial Set 7.5mm","proposed_clinical_subtitle":"Trial set for sizing stem extensions (75mm, 100mm, 150mm lengths)","proposed_conflict_detected":false,"proposed_enriched_at":"2026-03-28T06:24:16.442638+00:00","proposed_entity_type":"instrument","proposed_reasoning_summary":"Internal evidence clearly describes a trial instrument set for stem extensions used in orthopedic revision procedures. The brochure description explicitly states this is a set of trials (not implants) in three lengths (75mm, 100mm, 150mm) with 7.5mm diameter, used to select the appropriate final implant. Material is specified as surgical grade stainless steel, appropriate for reusable trial instruments. However, critical information is missing: (1) no brand/system identification, making it impossible to link to specific implant systems; (2) no specification of which joint (hip vs knee) or specific surgical indication; (3) no external verification possible. Stem extensions are typically used in revision hip or knee arthroplasty to bypass bone defects or achieve distal fixation. Confidence is moderate based on clear internal description but limited by missing system context. Requires review to identify parent implant system and complete anatomical/procedural classification.","proposed_recommended_action":"send_to_review","proposed_semantic_anatomy_scope":["Long Bone","Femur or Tibia"],"proposed_semantic_brand_system":"Unknown","proposed_semantic_coating_default":null,"proposed_semantic_confidence":0.65,"proposed_semantic_family_group":"Stem Extension Trial Set 7.5mm","proposed_semantic_implant_class":"Trial Instrument","proposed_semantic_material_default":"Stainless Steel (Surgical Grade)","proposed_semantic_parent_brand":"Unknown","proposed_semantic_procedure_scope":["Revision Arthroplasty","Joint Reconstruction"],"proposed_semantic_review_required":true,"proposed_semantic_system_type":"Orthopedic Trial Instrumentation","proposed_semantic_use_case_tags":["trial","sizing","stem extension","revision 